codex
The production paths are now grain-consistent: detail status compares canonical quantities, display fields remain entered-UoM, and MRP subtracts canonical shipped quantity from canonical ordered quantity. One test-quality concern remains: the new case/pallet MRP “regressions” currently call a local two-number subtraction helper rather than executing the SQL with case/pallet fixtures; I’m validating the runnable suites and checking whether any other test genuinely covers that query.
